{{primary sources|date=April 2013}}
The '''''German Dance Platform''''' ([[German language]]: ''Tanz Plattform Deutschland''), is a biennial [[contemporary dance]] [[festival]] held in different locations. The festival strives to bring together cultural [[event organizer]]s, [[Trade magazine|trade press]] and mainstream audiences from [[Germany]] and abroad.

The first edition took place in [[Berlin]], in 1994. The festival was created through the cooperation between various institutions working to support contemporary dance in [[Germany]].<ref name="Tanzplattform Deutschland">{{cite web|title=Tanzplattform Deutschland 1994|url=http://www.tanzplattform.de/1994|publisher=Tanzplattform Deutschland|accessdate=25 April 2013}}</ref> Other locations have included [[Frankfurt am Main]] (1996), [[Leipzig]] (2002), [[Düsseldorf]] (2004), [[Stuttgart]] (2006) and [[Dresden]] (2012).

