'''Terminus''' is a poem written by [[Ralph Waldo Emerson]]. Emerson wrote the poem in the latter stages of his life. In it, he refers to how time is the limit of human life.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Strauch|first=Carl F.|date=June 1950|title=The Date of Emerson's Terminus|journal=PMLA|volume=65|issue=4|pages=360–379|doi=10.2307/459643|jstor=459643}}</ref>

